> When an expression has multiple data types,
> 
> 
> Java automatically promotes smaller types to larger ones for safe calculation.
> 

---

### ðŸ§  Rule:

```java
byte â†’ short â†’ int â†’ long â†’ float â†’ double

```

---

### ðŸ“Œ Example 1:

```java
byte a = 10;
